verbose_text: However, these mechanisms cannot explain the lower insulin stimulated glucose uptake in primary adipocytes and certain types of skeletal muscle from the AS160-knockout mouse (XREF_FIG E, XREF_FIG F, XREF_FIG A and XREF_FIG B) because the theoretical truncated peptide of AS160 was not detectable and there was no full-length AS160 in the homozygous AS160-knockout mouse (XREF_FIG B- XREF_FIG D).
